notes.text:
Release of OpenShift Serverless 1.19.0

Red Hat Product Security has rated this update as having a security impact of Moderate. A Common Vulnerability Scoring System (CVSS) base score, which gives a detailed severity rating, is available for each vulnerability from the CVE link(s) in the References section.
notes.title: Topic

notes.text:
Red Hat OpenShift Serverless release of the OpenShift Serverless Operator. This version of the OpenShift Serverless Operator is supported on Red Hat OpenShift Container Platform versions 4.6, 4.7, 4.8 and 4.9, and includes security and bug fixes and enhancements. For more information, see the documentation listed in the References section.

Security Fix(es):

* golang: net/http/httputil: panic due to racy read of persistConn after handler panic (CVE-2021-36221)

For more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.

cwe.name: Concurrent Execution using Shared Resource with Improper Synchronization ('Race Condition')

notes.text: A race condition flaw was found in Go. The incoming requests body weren't closed after the handler panic and as a consequence this could lead to ReverseProxy crash.  The highest threat from this vulnerability is to Availability.
notes.title: Vulnerability description

notes.text: golang: net/http/httputil: panic due to racy read of persistConn after handler panic
notes.title: Vulnerability summary

notes.text:
* In Red Hat OpenStack Platform, because the flaw has a lower impact and the fix would require a substantial amount of development, no update will be provided at this time for the impacted RHOSP packages.

* In Service Telemetry Framework, because the flaw has a lower impact and the package is not directly used by STF1.3, no update will be provided at this time for the STF1.3 sg-core-container. Additionally, because Service Telemetry Framework1.2 will be retiring soon, no update will be provided at this time for the STF1.2 smart-gateway-container.
notes.title: Statement

notes.text: The CVSS score(s) listed for this vulnerability do not reflect the associated product's status, and are included for informational purposes to better understand the severity of this vulnerability.
notes.title: CVSS score applicability
